===Noun===
'''azure'''

# {{tincture}} A [[blue]] colour on a [[coat of arms]], represented in engraving by horizontal parallel lines.
#* '''1997''': In ''Bb'' [Glover's Roll], the conventional letter ''B'' is used to indicate '''azure''' in most items. &mdash; Brault, ''Early Blazon''
# The clear blue colour of the sky; also, a pigment or dye of this colour.
#:<table><tr><td>azure colour: &nbsp;</td><td bgcolor="#3372A8" width="80">&nbsp; </td></tr></table>
# The blue vault above; the unclouded sky.
# The [[lapis lazuli]].

